Pre-Game Insights: Gibraltar vs. Liechtenstein play the first match of the Nations League on Saturday, September 7, 2024, at 18:00 (local time) at the Europa Sports Complex.
Predictions favor Gibraltar to win based on their current form and Liechtenstein's recent loss to San Marino.
Gibraltar has a history of low-scoring games, with all their matches in the year being under 2.5 goals.
Liechtenstein also has a tendency for low-scoring games, with three out of five matches in 2024 being under 2.5 goals.
The match is expected to be aggressive, with the referee Kristo Tohver having a history of issuing more than four yellow cards in six of his last nine matches.
Gibraltar's probable lineup includes Banda; Olivero, Lopes, Jolley, and Annesley; Britto, Bent, and Torrilla; Walker, Scanlon, and De Barr.
Liechtenstein's probable lineup includes Buchel; Beck, Wieser, and Gopel; Wolfinger, Hasler, Buchel, Sele, and Zund; Loque-Notaro and Saglam.
